`useStore` uses `useSyncExternalStore(store.subscribe, store.get, store.get)` with no selector. Every component that calls `usePrefs()`, `useAllProgress()`, or `useBookProgress(id)` re-renders whenever **any** key in that store changes — e.g. marking chapter 3 of Book A as read re-renders the progress hooks in every `BookCard` for every other book on the Library page, plus `ContinueStrip`, plus `BookMap`/`Reader` if mounted.

**Fix** — add a selector-based subscribe so components only re-render when their slice changes:
```ts
export function useStore<T extends object, S = T>(
  store: Store<T>,
  selector: (s: T) => S = (s) => s as unknown as S,
): S {
  return useSyncExternalStore(
    store.subscribe,
    () => selector(store.get()),
    () => selector(store.get()),
  )
}
```
Then in `progress.ts`:
```ts
export function useBookProgress(bookId: string): BookProgress {
  return useStore(store, (all) => sanitize(all[bookId]))
}
```
This alone eliminates most of the unnecessary re-render cascade below.

```tsx
function BookCard({ book, step }: { book: Book; step?: number }) {
  const all = useAllProgress()        // subscribes to the WHOLE progress store
  const progress = all[book.id]
  const stats = bookStats(book)       // recomputed from scratch every render
```
With N books rendered, one `toggleChapterRead` anywhere re-renders all N cards and recomputes `bookStats` N times, even though only one book's stats/progress actually changed.

**Fix**: use the (now selector-based) `useBookProgress(book.id)` instead of `useAllProgress()`, and wrap `BookCard` in `React.memo`:
```tsx
const BookCard = memo(function BookCard({ book, step }: { book: Book; step?: number }) {
  const progress = useBookProgress(book.id)
  const stats = useMemo(() => bookStats(book), [book])
  ...
})
```

`src/lib/content.ts:61-71, 154-164`. `books` and `categories` are frozen at module load (`import.meta.glob(..., { eager: true })`), yet:
- `getBook` and `booksInCategory` do a linear `.find`/`.filter` scan every call.
- `bookStats(b)` recalculates word counts and reduces over all chapters every call — called repeatedly for the same book across `Library`'s `BookCard`, `totals`, and `BookMap`.

**Fix** — precompute once at module scope since the source data never changes:
```ts
const booksById = new Map(books.map((b) => [b.id, b]))
const booksByCategory = new Map<string, Book[]>()
for (const b of books) {
  const arr = booksByCategory.get(b.categoryId) ?? []
  arr.push(b); booksByCategory.set(b.categoryId, arr)
}
export function getBook(id?: string) { return id ? booksById.get(id) : undefined }
export function booksInCategory(categoryId: string) { return booksByCategory.get(categoryId) ?? [] }

const statsCache = new Map<string, BookStats>()
export function bookStats(b: Book): BookStats {
  const cached = statsCache.get(b.id)
  if (cached) return cached
  const stats = /* existing calc */
  statsCache.set(b.id, stats)
  return stats
}
```

`src/lib/content.ts:110` `loadChapter` re-runs the markdown loader, section-splitting regex, and `mdToHtml` (marked.parse) every single time a chapter route is visited — including hitting "Next"/"Prev" back and forth in `Reader.tsx`, which re-parses the same static markdown repeatedly.

**Fix** — memoize by `${bookId}:${n}` since chapter files are static build-time content:
```ts
const chapterCache = new Map<string, Chapter>()
export async function loadChapter(bookId: string, n: number): Promise<Chapter | null> {
  const key = `${bookId}:${n}`
  const cached = chapterCache.get(key)
  if (cached) return cached
  const loader = chapterIndex.get(bookId)?.get(n)
  if (!loader) return null
  // ...existing parse logic...
  const chapter = { number: n, title, words, minutes, keyIdeas, bodyHtml: mdToHtml(bodyMd), inPractice }
  chapterCache.set(key, chapter)
  return chapter
}
```

`src/lib/markdown.tsx:12-17` — `mdToHtml(text)` runs inline in the render body with no memoization. `BookMap` renders one `Markdown` per chapter via `MapChapterCard` (`BookMap.tsx:158-166`); combined with issue #1, toggling read-state on chapter 3 re-renders `BookMap` → re-renders all `MapChapterCard`s → re-parses markdown for **every** chapter's summary again, not just the one that changed.

**Fix**: memoize the parse, and memoize the card component:
```tsx
export function Markdown({ text, className }: { text: string; className?: string }) {
  const html = useMemo(() => mdToHtml(text), [text])
  return <div className={className ? `md ${className}` : 'md'} dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: html }} />
}
```
